\v 10 \w The|strong="H3068"\w* \w man|strong="H6030"\w* \w who|strong="H3068"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w there|strong="H5975"\w* among \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w myrtle|strong="H1918"\w* \w trees|strong="H1918"\w* \w said|strong="H6030"\w*, “\w These|strong="H7971"\w* \w are|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w ones|strong="H5975"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w Lord|strong="H3068"\w* \w has|strong="H3068"\w* \w sent|strong="H7971"\w* \w out|strong="H7971"\w* \w to|strong="H1980"\w* \w patrol|strong="H1980"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* earth.”
\v 11 \w The|strong="H3605"\w* riders\f + \fr 1:11 \ft Implied. \f* reported \w to|strong="H1980"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w angel|strong="H4397"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w Lord|strong="H3068"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w among|strong="H3427"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w myrtle|strong="H1918"\w* \w trees|strong="H1918"\w*, “\w We|strong="H1980"\w* \w have|strong="H3068"\w* \w been|strong="H8252"\w* patrolling \w the|strong="H3605"\w* earth \w and|strong="H1980"\w* \w saw|strong="H2009"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w whole|strong="H3605"\w* earth \w has|strong="H3068"\w* \w been|strong="H8252"\w* \w pacified|strong="H8252"\w*.\f + \fr 1:11 \ft “Pacified.” In the context this “peace” has more to do with being forced into submission and defeat than a time of harmony and tranquility. It could be compared to the imposed “Pax Romana” of later times in which the Romans asserted their control over the nations they had defeated militarily and brought “peace.”\f*”
\p 
