\v 15 \w and|strong="H1419"\w* \w I|strong="H5921"\w* am extremely \w angry|strong="H7107"\w* \w with|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* arrogant \w nations|strong="H1471"\w* \w who|strong="H1992"\w* think \w they|strong="H1992"\w* \w are|strong="H1992"\w* secure. \w I|strong="H5921"\w* \w was|strong="H7451"\w* only \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w little|strong="H4592"\w* \w angry|strong="H7107"\w* \w with|strong="H5921"\w* \w my|strong="H5921"\w* \w people|strong="H1471"\w*,\f + \fr 1:15 \ft “With my people” implied.\f* \w but|strong="H1992"\w* \w they|strong="H1992"\w* made \w the|strong="H5921"\w* punishment \w far|strong="H5921"\w* \w worse|strong="H7451"\w*.\f + \fr 1:15 \ft In other words God had allowed the heathen nations to punish his people because of their sins, but these nations went too far in their attacks.\f*
\p 
