\b
\c 3
\p 
\v 1 \w Then|strong="H5975"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \w Lord|strong="H3068"\w*\f + \fr 3:1 \ft Literally, “he” which could refer either to the Lord or the angel previously mentioned.\f* \w showed|strong="H7200"\w* \w me|strong="H6440"\w* \w Joshua|strong="H3091"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \w high|strong="H1419"\w* \w priest|strong="H3548"\w* \w standing|strong="H5975"\w* \w before|strong="H6440"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \w angel|strong="H4397"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \w Lord|strong="H3068"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w Satan|strong="H7854"\w*\f + \fr 3:1 \ft Satan means “the accuser.” \f* \w standing|strong="H5975"\w* \w on|strong="H5921"\w* \w his|strong="H3068"\w* \w right|strong="H3225"\w* accusing \w him|strong="H6440"\w*.
